reviews.text: The food was good but the overall experience could be better. We found hair in our appetizers but that didn’t really bother us. The service is kinda slow or they just don’t know when to come to table to take our orders. The somas were still good! The butter chicken was good! Nann wasn’t bad. If you want to get your money worth go during buffet but I wouldn’t go during dinner just my opinion. Spent 95 dollars for 5 people which isn’t bad. The food use to be much better I believe but no idea if management change/chef.

OVERALL:
The aroma of the spices and the tandoori smokiness of the meat dishes were a beautiful compliment to their vegetarian meals.

MENU:
There is a wide variety for even the pickiest of eaters without losing the authentic taste of Southern Indian Cuisine.

NOTE:
The service is a bit introverted yet pleasant, have patience with them as they are quite gracious people.

Definitely a must visit when you are in the area!

Ordered Takeout lamb biryani and kadai paneer.
Biryani was good portion and tasty, lamb was tender.
Kadai paneer was ok less saucy was expecting more gravy.
Minerva just opened back after renovation..but worth try .

Today, I ordered (#82C7BCD8)
Butter Chicken, Chilly Paneer and Paneer Kadhai.

I have to throw out the Chilly Paneer as all of the pieces were not cooked. They were raw and NOT CHEWABLE.

Food was for the family. My daughter couldn't eat it at all.

My wife was sick so I ordered the food.
She was not able to eat half of the Naan as it was too thick.

I am really disappointed. At one point I thought I should return the food. The only reason I didn't is because I live 8 miles away from the place.

What I ordered was common dishes.
And even those you can't make good. (At least eatble)
I come here often to get carry out. The food is always fresh and tasty and the entrées are large! I recommend using the restaurant's website to order.

After I tried to search for nice Italian restaurants got a while in my area for while, finally I found Fontina Grill where is good choice. They are chosen in top ten best restaurants in Montgomery county, MD recently. I have no question why. It is not too formal restaurant but make you feel impressive and comfortable. Inside is clean, organize, nice decoration. Outside restaurant makes me feel like a Cafe. I decided to came here because I really want to try Spagetti Cabonnara with blackened chicken brest that I couldn't find this dish at most Italian restaurants around here, for some reason, also pesto pasta dish (with grilled chicken breast). But Fontina Grill have both. They still has a lot of choices of Italian food in their menu including pasta, sandwich/burger and homemade pizza. Absolutely I will come back and try all of them soon after I was very enjoy my meal today and service is fairly good. I spent around $51 (plus tax and tip) for two lunch dishes with free bread appetizer. The price seem a little high but you get what you pay, I guess. Not a big deal though because they were quite big portion that you can even take some home for another meal.

The only thing that might bothered me was the parking quite limited.

Great service. Excellent food! I have been here twice and love the old school feel of a great wait staff that know the finer point of service, like, to pour a bottle of wine and let you taste it. The food is just perfect.
Ordered the Seafood Rose and it was very delicious. Also had the carrot cake and that was good too. Portions were a nice size. Staff was efficient and attentive. Overall it was a good experience.

Visited 9.23.22

Restaurant has great food, plenty of choices, and the waiter (Reza?) was attentive and very nice. Parking is ample too. Free bread is very good.
Solid choice for casual Italian food. Pleasant outdoor seating in a quiet area. Complimentary bread was top notch and unlimited! However the white truffle pizza was far too cheesy.

I just left this subway & I must say it's the worst location I've ever been to the lady making the sandwich acted like she didn't even want to make the sandwich then I had to tell her that she needed to put extra stuff in the sandwich because it was  one of there new sandwiches & it seem like she didn't even know how to make it .  I asked to use the restroom which was clearly locked & asked her for a key & she said someone was in there which was a lie because I was in  there for almost 40 mins & no one ever came out so really they don't want people using the women's restroom but they have a giant sign on the door that says for paying customers only so I had to use the men's restroom be for I left .. I will never go back to this location again  the sandwich wasn't even good .  The location I went to the following day in Germantown was 100 times better & I got the exact same sandwich  & there price are higher that the location in Germantown .. So I would NOT recommend this location to anyone !!!

This Subway went Downhill. I a 12" Turkey and got my wife a 6" Italian. Both of us were disappointed. Both our breads were chewy like it was old and maybe days old. To lazy to take them back so we just tossed them in the trash. Won't be going to that one again. The Subway here in Germantown, Maryland off of Great Seneca Highway is 1,000,000 times better.

Their food made me sick yesterday. To start I was standing there a while before the employee stopped cleaning to acknowledge me being there. Fast forward a couple hours after eating my sub and I'm dealing with food poisoning. Now that I think about it I don't recall the employee changing her gloves between finishing the cleaning and preparing that sub...

Went to the store to pickup an order.  The order couldn't be found.  Instead of checking the receipt or trying to work it out, we were screamed at and put out of the store.  Other customers stopped us in the parking lot to tell us how shocked they were at the unprovoked behavior.  Our company regularly orders from this location for classes and meetings.  They will never get another penny of our money or any of the employees.  Abhorrent treatement.  If there was a 'zero' star, I would use it.

The worst subway in the area. management is rude. And tries to get as much money out of you as possible. He refused to take. My coupon because it was on my phone which I download it. And the website clearly said turn your phone sideways. So the cashier can see the whole coupon. Which I showed him the coupon and he said I do not take those coupons because it's not paper. And I try pointing out What the website told me to do. And he still refused To serve me. And started telling me hes the owner and he doesn't have to take any coupons if he doesn't want too. I'll be reporting him and filing a complain on him to corporate tomorrow when they open. There was a customer paying when I got there and I over heard them arguing over extra napkins because the customer wanted a few more napkins.  ridiculous He is super stingy.

I ordered the chicken club for my boyfriend today and when he took a bite into it, it was NOT done it was literally RAW! I called the Wendy’s and it just goes to voicemail. I spent 28 dollars and they made me pull in a parking spot because they were still cooking the sandwich which was not done . I am truly disgusted.

This place was horrible. Waited over 15 minutes. Was the only Caucasian people in the store and everyone else was waited on as we were invisible I guess. Not once did anyone even speak to us and say someone will be with you shortly. Absolutely nothing. Very disrespectful. I will be contacting a corporate representative. And then we get home my fiancé has a Caesar salad and that’s it just the salad no dressing , no sides.
Lettuce and Chicken. Anyone who knows me knows I get along with just about anyone and today was a total slap in the face. I frequent this store but after today they will never get my business again and honestly Wendy’s may have lost a customer for good.
We ordered 2 bourbon bacon cheeseburger meals and it came out to be $30 and the burger looked and tasted old. Look at this picture.
Their new drive thru cashier is the slowest. There's always a long line and 20 mins wait whenever shes working because she can't take order and take payment at the same time
We came here for the breakfast. They intentionally closed the inside to have only drive thru orders. And the lady gave us a nasty lady when we asked for my credit card back…

Always so fresh and delicious! The portions are big and the staff are friendly!

Edit: Originally 5 stars, but decreased to 3. After our most recent visit, we found a metal wire in our food.
My favorite fast food place. Lady at the front desk who takes the orders is always very kind and helpful.

I can guarantee you the best chicken and cheese quesadilla you will find is right here in Rockville. I highly recommend it. It has fresh ingredients, it tastes authentic, and it comes with chips, sour cream and fresh guacamole 🥑
Food was not so tasty. But I like the salsas they have.
Very friendly and patient cashier and explained Very well who is not familiar with Mexican menu's.

One of my husband's favorite burger place! We had a quick drive-thru before going to DC for July 4th. The service was fast and we were well accomodated. The burgers and fries are so good and recommended if you're looking for a taste from the South.

I'm pretty sure if you ordered $100 worth of food, they would still have it to the window in 60 seconds flat. The staff here are absolute machines and crank out burgers, fries, and chicken faster than modern physics can explain. The food is consistent. It's not a Michelin star joint, so don't go there if that's what you're expecting.

I'm the only one in line around 9 PM on a Thursday and I get handed two sloppy wet lettuce-soaked spicy chicken sandwiches that taste microwaved a few times. Even with the need for late-night cravings driving here for your fix is not recommended as advertised.  I've had way better checkers' experience with fresh meals made with pride for the most part. Not expecting too much for $10 but still.

Whoever the guy is running the late night drive through needs a raise. He’s always juggling a line of cards and payments seamlessly. Even when things get slightly messed up he is great about fixing it right away. I specially drive out of my way to this checkers because of the customer service here

Editing my previous review and increasing too stars seems like they are taking my compliant seriously today the order was perfect and very fresh. This is what I like to see. If I’m future visits they continue to get it right I’ll edit again to give full 5 stars.

This is the Maryland Sichuan food restaurant I go to for Sichuan Food. I was born and grow up in Chengdu. The food here here is authentic Chengdu food. Just like what I may have at home. Also the Cantonese food here is very good. The signature dish Gui Fei Chicken is a must try in the Cantonese menu. The other dishes are delicious too. Ask the very Friendly Maggie, and I am sure she can give suitable recommendations. The photos on the wall are authentic pictures of Sichuan street scenes (old times and new; rural or urban) by photographer Chen Jin. Check them out when you’re in the restaurant.

I have been going there for over 15 years. I don't know if any ownership has changed but every time I have visited and eaten there it has been great. The food is consistently good and the waitresses are always friendly and attentive.

Probably would never come back again order shrimp with lobster sauce but it's not the same as before. Never had someone throw in black bean with the dish. The price is ridiculous expensive. Definitely not worth the money.

China Jade Rockville breaks the "Chinese Food stereotype". LOVE both their Sichuanese and Cantonese dishes! I have never tried any other restaurant with such wide variety and yet still perfect each dish. Even the ingredients used are fresh and tasty, unlike many other Chinese restaurants.

1) Fish with pickled vegetable soup (鲜椒酸汤鱼片) - SICHUANESE. There are 2 dishes like this, one with fresh chilli and sweet potato noodles, which is what we ordered. My favorite soup! So rich and they used real broth. Perfect for the cold weather. 2) Sauteed Fish Filet with Vegetables (翡翠鱼片) - CANTONESE. I normally hate snow peas but this dish is so good. The snow peas are perfectly flavored and crunchy. 3) Beef & Beef Tendon with Szechuan/Sichuan Spicy Sauce (夫妻肺片) - SICHUANESE. very authentic and famous Sichuanese appetizer. Different kinds of spices immersed in the meat, making it perfectly and uniquely flavorful. I always order this when I come. Favorite spicy appetizer. Even though it's appetizer, the portion is SO BIG. This itself makes a full meal. 4) Spicy Chengdu Style Bull Frogs (香辣馋嘴牛蛙). The chinese name directly translates into "yummy, mouth-watering". It's my favorite frog dish I have ever eaten. Perfectly seasoned with signature spices. The meat taste like chicken if you have never tried it. The cucumbers and bamboo shoots are crunchy, too.

This Chinese restaurant specializes in spicy/Mandarin food but the things we ordered were not even that spicy--was more watered-down. They does offer a few selections of Cantonese dishes but they were okay. Also, their portions were a tad on the smaller size.

Though this restaurant is pretty clean and has good service.
Customer service is awesome. Sarita make my Coffee better then I.. the cashier she is a latina super friendly place is always clean
They were very busy but still delivered great customer service and we had our food and drinks in a timely manner
This place is very busy. Great customer service and varieties stuffs to choice from.

I tried ordering online and the app said they were not taking online orders at that time even though I was attempting to place an order 15 minutes before closing. I went in to place my order and they said they were closed. I asked at what time they close and they said at 3. I told them it was 2:45 and they said they close early to desinfect their working space. If that's the case, then modify your store hours. There is no need to trick customers or have them guessing
into your business to then tell them is closed. The staff was very unprofessional and rude. That is the type of service you will receive at dunkin nowadays. Not stepping a foot into any of their locations anymore.
Busy location in the AM. However staff is on top of orders and service to  ensure short wait times

Made mobile order for pickup in advance. Arrived about ten minutes later, the order was still in packing. The black coffee was warm as usual. Two breakfast biscuits were within standard. The hash browns were crispy as expected. This Burger King shares the building with two other shops - the Ripieno's Italian Bistro and the Jo Jo's.

Hey everybody, the burger king at gaithersburg just got a major makeover. Not only is it bigger, there are also two other restaurants added to this place, Ripieno's Italian bistro and Jojo's. And at these restaurants, you can order submarine sandwiches, pizza, grilled 🐔, filet mignon and have a salad 🥗 at jojo's salad bar. They even replaced the old seating area with dining room seats. So if you want to have lunch or dinner at burger king, you gotta go to this one in gaithersburg. This place is awesome!!

My girlfriend never received her food or drink. I ordered a Delux Chicken Sandwhich which was supposed to have mayo and veggies on it. I paid extra for veggies & cheese.  They delivered an undercooked piece of chicken pink in the middle on UNtoasted RIPPED buns with 0-veggies, 0-mayo and 0-cheese.    AVOID THIS LOCATION. If they are so careless with orders they will probably cause you to catch COVID by being unsanitary as well. Review also posted to yelp with pictures.

Since this Burger King has opened I've tired out JoJo's and Ripineo's both restaurants in the Burger King are great. JoJo's has a great deal for a crab cake sandwich 10.99 +tax comes with fries. Ripineo's has awesome sandwiches plus these crazy large slices of pizza $8 + tax for a cheese and $9 + tax for the pepperoni. The one in the picture came out to be $42 and some change. It fed 8 adults.

Came In for a big king XL and it was made for me. Went back a week or so later and they claim they haven't made it it months, and that they don't have ingredients.  So I told them it's just a double whopper with cheese ,pickles onions, lettuce and big king sauce... they said they can't make it for me. Mean while the big king burger can be made for me instead. What a joke.  🤦‍♂️  I went to all other burger King and they make it with no questions asked.

The morning crew is more professional then the evening crew. Senior leadership should be placed on the evening shift to get the younger employees and shift management up to speed on consistent professionalism.
Family owned deli. Their sandwiches are a great value made with fresh and high quality ingredients. Can’t go wrong

I did a google search to find a nice salad and this came up. My husband and I met for lunch and it did not disappoint!! I had the chipotle chicken wrap, it was delicious and fresh!!! Hubby opted for the steak and cheese and he also said it was very good. There was a nice selection of drinks and chips as well as prepackaged fruit bowels. The staff were very nice and patient as we browsed the menu. It’s close to work so I will definitely go again.

Just discovered this place and it will definitely be my new go-to! Friendly service, reasonable prices, quality food. I’ve been two days in a row and got the chicken salad sandwich and chipotle chicken wrap. Both were fantastic. Highly recommend, great for a quick lunch break!
I was wondering what to get for lunch one day, I ended up with a sandwich from here. It was a good move, definitely recommend.
Jin and the crew at Carvings are the best!  They always make us feel so welcome and the food is delicious!
I heard that this place recently changed ownership. The new owner was the head chef at another restaurant. I love the sashimi combo and the dancing yellow tail. Highly recommend.
Have a wonderful dinner with my friends!  I love sexy Jalapeno , spicy and tasty! Sushi and sashimi’s all delicious:) we will come back again !!!!
Fresh and delicious, it's definitely the best sushi in the area.
Literally the best sushi ever, the portion sizes are amazing. The fish is always delicious and fresh. I love the salmon combo. Even delivered, its amazing.
Excellent service and clean space. The sushi was fresh and delicious. One of the best places I have been! Try the mochi…it’s amazing!! We will be back for sure!

If I could give this place a zero I would. They sell counterfeit vaping products, that look like the real things. When I told them about this they denied any knowledge and refused to give me my money back. Be careful buying anything from here.

The owner is a bit of an opportunist and will exploit any opportunity that he can to make or save some money and advance his business. I moved my car while the nozzle was still inserted and caused the nozzle to fall out onto the ground. There was no damage (I had photographic evidence of this below) to either the hose or the nozzle, but apparently the whole staff of the station flooded out to catch me and file an insurance claim. The owner seems to have some kind of crony inspector on call as he was able to inspect and change out the whole hose and nozzle (complements of my insurance) within about an hour and a half (so fast that no independent inspection could possibly confirm whether or not there was any damage). The owner later explained to me that "insurance companies don't care about paying for new hoses and nozzles" and that he files these claims constantly "to keep his equipment in perfect condition."
My insurance rates haven't gone up, but I won't give any future business to this station, not only because I found the insurance claim to be unethical and exploitive, but because I can only imagine how else such an opportunistic business might take advantage of me. At least there are plenty of gas stations out there that are more neighborly than this.

Pulled in to grab something was finishing my conversation a on the side of store as some man in a silver pick up is honking telling me to move my car. I finish my conversation as im walking in hes walking out. I tell him you don't need to tell me to move my car I was finishing my conversation. He stated he was the owner and told me I could go to another store. Super rude worst experience ever. Wouldn't recommend anyone go spend there money here.

If I could rate zero for this place that's what it would be. Store employee is terrible!!!!!!!! Manager was even more worthless!!!  Can't help but to laugh at how incompetent this store is. Not only did they sell me a horrible, old pack of Dutch masters. They charged me $9 for a pack of 5 and they were old as dirt!  When I walked back into the store to demand a refund or exchange they said because I walked out of the store there was nothing they would do.
I did not even leave the parking lot and they still said no. NEVER SHOP HERE FOR GAS OR STORE ITEMS. OVER PRICED, TERRIBLE STORE PRESENTATION AND LACK OF TRAINING.

GOOD LUCK.

If I could post a zero I would.  I experienced a tire blow out on the highway and managed to limp into this gas station.  They told me I could park in their lot and wait for assistance but they were not happy about it.  After waiting an hour, I realized my lunch needed ice or it would spoil.  I took a small Ziploc snack bag into the shop.  As I walked toward the ice machine the two clerks became hostile "MA'AM, what do you think you're doing?"

"Getting some ice so my lunch won't spoil in the heat".
"You better pay $1.00 for that ice"
"Ok, sure.  Let me go out to my completely disabled car and grab my purse."
"No.  Put the ice down now. You cannot leave the store with that ice."
"I am not stealing the ice.  I would like to put it with my food and I will grab a dollar out of my bag as well.  I cannot drive away without paying, obviously".

The man stands in front of the door with his arms folded and tells me to drop the ice, go to my car, get my money, and then come back.  He would not let other customers exit or enter until I put this tiny bag of ice down.  Did they offer to help me change my spare tire?  Ask if I was OK after nearly crashing on the highway? NO.

Way to set the human race back a couple of steps on the evolutionary trail guys!

The triple cheese burger I had looked a bit like a mess but it was tasty and hot. The fries were good, salted and served hot.

The staff were very polite. There was a bit of a wait for the drive though but after a few minutes it sped up.
Mrs Zeena has been so patient & kind during my dining experience I appreciate her so much, I look forward to my next visit with More of my Family
One of the better McDonald’s in the area. Always has my order right & they are friendly.

After 11pm this is by far the WORSE McDonald's to come to! I've waited in the drive thru over 30 mins, when I ordered from the app!

The only take the first speaker on this drive throu, they'll constantly tell the second one to hold on and never get back to you. I've gone in twice was cussed out the first time I asked about my food by a young Spanish boy that was working at the time. Screaming to my face calling me a B****! Not understanding that time I waited over an hour!

Online orders can not get refunded, so you all should tend to online as priority! This wait time is seriously ridiculously because when going in, you'll see nothing but order bags lying around! Smh & it's over 4 people working!!

Someone make this make sense please!

AVOID THIS MCDONALD'S
Good location. Well mannered staffs. Seems newly opened. Very nice neat and clean place.
The pizza is so good! I always come back for the Sicilian. 10/10 recommend! :)

Good pizza but I would stay away from the calzones as they look better than they taste.

The pizza has a nice chewy crust and I would return again for the pizza.

The calzone, however, was very much bleh. They seem to use mozzarella and cheddar cheese along with some ricotta. Also not very much meat. Very disappointed with the calzone.
Great pizza, we had the Sicilian cheese pizza, it’s was huge
yummy yummy pizza,  I got fresh garlic and pineapple, so good, very reasonable for the amount of food.

Gotta be honest. We purchased 3 pizza's from them and a calzone. The calzone was slightly better but not by much. I do not know what they make their pizza with but, I suggest not buying it. Me and my entire family were disgusted with the taste of it, couldnt finish the first slice. We have very low quality taste, like freezer chicken nuggets every night...we're no food critics here. But it was bad. And we ordered more than one pizza so I know it wasn't just an accident. Not to mention the absurdity that was our digestive tracks after eating it. A hair above food poisoning I'd say. Maybe their other food is good and that's why they have 4.2 stars🤷🏽‍♀️ but whatever you do don't buy the pizza you'll get food poisoning, or much worse.(one single redeeming quality was that the delivery of food was super quick and the person very nice don't know if they worked for the restaurant or not though)

I've lived in 5 southern states and this place has the BEST brisket I've ever had. The owner said it was smoked for 18 hours; it tasted like heaven. The wings were super flavorful and the meat just falls of the bone.

The mac n cheese was creamy and had a nice slight spice to it. I loved that it was not just sprinkled cheese over oiled noodles like you get with most places.

This is more than five star food; this is five star treatment as well! Cameron, the owner’s son, went out of his way to graciously answer all of my questions and cooked all of the food I purchased immediately before I had scheduled to pick it up. Who does that!?  :)

The food was truly exceptional. The ribs were done to perfection. I am obsessed with the smokehouse wings (pic shows sauce on side), and the slaw, mac, and cornbread were phenomenal. Hands down the best spot for bona-fide Barbecue!

This food is solid.  I am from the South and prefer charcoal to smoke, but I'd eat here again.  The brisket was tender, pulled pork pretty good, cole slaw was different, but not bad at all.  Seemed to have a mustard/vinegar base. All in all, we liked it.
Omg! Delicious! Ordered pony express and sliced briskets. And its really good! Freshly cooked! Lots of flavors!
I had the pulled chicken sandwich which was very tender and the sauce very good. But the mac and cheese and potato salad were just bland. They definitely need a new recipe for those dishes.

It seems like every time i come to this location the price on the screen does not match the price that they give you at the first window when using discount codes or reward points. And it seems to happen on a particular shift. The lady at the first window argued me down that i was incorrect and kept shutting the window as i tried to explain that the prices was not adding up. I will drive the extra miles to another store. Food was ok, fries was harder than arithmetic

Service is fast when using the in-store kiosks and the oeders are almost always 100% correct. The dining area is usually clean but seating is a bit limited when dining in and is sometimes taken by people who are just hanging out.

Ordered the big breakfast hot platter. Sliced the egg in half and saw disgusting MOLD EVERYWHERE!! Left feedback for the restaurant via the complaint form online and over the phone, still have not heard back. Absolutely mortified and concerned about the quality and safety of food this establishment is serving to the public!

This McDonald's has very poor customer service. The wait is always extreamly long in the drive through line and going inside to order is just as bad. The employees that work are carefree, disrespectful and  always getting the food order wrong. It's unfortunate that this place has such bad customer service and it stems from management.
Drive through experience - it is faster than other McDonald's. The people are friendly. This Mcdonald was recently remodeled. It looks great inside and is comfortable to seat and eat.
Fuel is fuel. Asked to use the restroom while I was filling up and was lied to by the clerk stating they do not have a restroom. He’s a liar, I’ve used the bathroom here before.
Bad customer service, not very helpful when it  comes to service for gas or working on cars, they don't car they just want the money, don't care about their customers, the manager or owner is rude

There is absolutely no customer service from the owner Russell. As a first time customer he treated me like dirt. He bragged about how he does 12 hour days while the shop is only open 7-4 daily. I like to support family owned businesses but Russell Dodson is arrogant, mouthy, and plain rude. I won’t even go back for gas and I advise everyone else to stay away!!
Overpriced.  Never have a available restroom.

I was looking at a used car at Rockville Lexus and needed a second opinion. I took the car to the Mechanics located at the Shell. There were 2 younger guys working at the shop. They had time to look at the car and put it on the lift. They charged me a half hour worth of work to over look it which was well worth it. They were very professional. They even let me look at the car from the lift view and gave me their opinion on the vehicle and answered any questions I had. Outstanding service! If I lived closer I would bring all my vehicles to them.
Great food! Workers were very kind and I loved the vibe of the place.

My husband and I had lunch h here and the food was delicious. Juanita was so friendly and very witty  (my husband can be a comedian) and she was time enough for his jokes.  Overall I would definitely go back.
Delicious food and amazing service!

We love Juanita's. My kids love their pupusas and I love the chicken fajita. The chicken burrito is one of my favorites too, it's a hearty burrito that my youngest can't finish. The have other authentic tasty Mexican which is unlike Tex Mex and the Salvadorean food is home style. I will continue to go to Juanita's Restaurant. They are open now for take out so I recommend you try it.

Im usually searching for a really awesome pupusa place, but not a fan at all. SUPER salty. There’s too much flower, which makes it more of a tortilla with flavoring. The “curtido” (i think that’s how you spell it) tastes old. And something about the 12 pupusas also taste old. My family and I couldn’t even finish them and just ordered something else . A waste of my money.

Very good, traditional style pizza at a carry out joint with quick, competent service - 5 stars for the pizza and service because both were great and 3 stars for the atmosphere because it's counter service carry out with a utilitarian atmosphere because that's all they need.

Contrary to what you'll see on the business page, this location is take out only - there are only a few chairs available in the store while you wait. That being said, we ordered and received our pizza within 15 minutes, so the wait wasn't too bad. The pizza was pretty standard and didn't have anything to "wow" me, but it still tastes pretty good. I highly recommend ordering ahead and picking up your food rather than waiting in store.

Raw chicken was sold when we call back the manager ( at least he said he was the manager) very very rude un apologetic and literally said I was lying. This place was recommended by a neighbor . We had gotten their pizza but this time added the chicken to the greatest disappointment!! Thank God we didn’t give it to the toddler. I will certainly reach out to consumers report as well
This location has great food. On Mondays you can get a pizza for $10

If Google let me give 10 stars I would. Rhonda was a sweetheart on the phone and the delivery driver Millard was prompt and polite. Food came fast and piping hot. Pasta and chicken were cooked perfectly. My new go to place when I travel here for work. Well done Milano's your pride shows.

Great experience, food was delicious!!
My first time here , our server Anthony was on point, he had good knowledge of the menu and his suggestion was delicious and well made. If you are Peruvian and you are missing the flavors of home this is the place to go!! And on top of that they have a good selection of Peruvian wines , beer , products and desserts. I hope to be back soon.

I haven’t tried many items, but the regular ceviche de pescado is very good here!  I am very particular about the flavor of the leche de tigre in my ceviche but Barra Brava has the perfect flavor, not strong yet not too weak. A lot of Peruvian restaurants in the area have trouble finding the perfect blend, but not at Barra Brava. I can’t wait to try another dish next time!

I live close to this place but only made it in recently. The food was extra surprisingly good! We were not expecting it to be that good! We got the mussels, which was piled with onions and garlic inside. Almost like a ceviche muddle dish. We also got the fish dish which has a great sauce and plenty of thick chunks of onions. It said it had sweet potatoes but they seemed like regular. They also have a 3.8% discount when using cash, including alcohol. The only issue I had was they said 20 minutes, and it was closer to 40 minutes. When waiting with a baby in the tight space it made things difficult. Although there were maybe 10 to go dishes coming out. I just think they should give an accurate time if they are busier. Also some of the wine looks pretty old, with shriveled lables and some have dust. Bottles of wine seemed a little higher priced too.  Otherwise they do have a great selection of authentic Peruvian ice cream.
This place is a small quaint Bodega-type restaurant.  It has limited very parking and inside seating, however, the food is amazing!  The dishes are excellently plated and just delicious!

Went here with my wife and her family for the Peruvian independence day. I wasn’t sure what to expect because my wife said we were coming for the seafood. After reading some reviews I was hopeful and was pleasantly surprised.

Only one of us ordered their “famous” ceviche but everyone loved their food. Space is limited and even though they sell alcohol, they can’t sell it to you to have on premise which was annoying but nonetheless everything was delicious.

I had the arroz con mariscos and it was delicious though I wasn’t expecting how spicy the rice was. If you’re sensitive to spice careful about what you ordered although I think mine was an exception.

Definitely coming back to try some of the more traditional criolla dishes though 🤤🤌🏼
